- Halagen, Karana <br>
<br>
18-21 aviak guards LR <br>
22-25 varrious LOIO<br>
<br>
Contrary to what some may think, enchanters can make great soloers. I have an enchanter who is currently level 25 on Karana server. Here is my guide for levels 18-25 <br>
<br>
Here is the basic method:<br>
1. tash mob<br>
2. charm mob<br>
3. tash another mob<br>
4. root 2nd mob get 1st to attack 2nd. 5. once root/charm breaks, stun and reapply (if both break, i hope you have sow/jboots cause we cant tank all that well, if your level 20 keep illusion troll up or cast rune I or rune II to keep hps up)<br>
6. once 1st mob dead, invis and nuke 2nd mob dead<br>
<br>
If you chose two mobs of similar level, the 2nd mob may even be 'running' once you cast invis which makes it very easy to kill <br>
<br>
For this stategy I suggest you do not attemp without sow/jboots as it can turn bad <br>
<br>
Here is where I hunted: <br>
* 18-21 aviak guards in lake rathe (arena is good for begginers since aviaks can be pulled one at a time and zone is near if it turns bad) <br>
* 22-25 lake of ill omen - you can find many mobs waiting to be killed around the undead ruins area. If you have good charisma gear such as myself (171 cha with buff) then i suggest charming mobs which are yellow or even red, wear them down with some smaller mobs and then wait for your just rewards when you finally get to kill that sucker. but I am finding at level 25 now, having to use beguile is much more mana consuming and yellow/reds are resisting more, so stick to whites vs white/blues. <br>
<br>
The tashan line of spells means that enchanters can be one of the best solo classes at these early levels. I have played a shaman up to level 60, and soloing was easy, but never as fast as with my enchanter. Taking on a red mob and getting two blue bubbles of exp including the exp from when your red mob killed other mobs, is much better than the shaman method of soloing blues one after the other, usually would take 4 or 5 medium fights to get the same exp as the one fight as an enchanter, and breeze makes downtime even less (cant wait for 29 and clarity ) <br>
<br>
I hope you all enjoy this method as much as I have, i am leveling so fast i cant keep up with all my research spells, omen is a good place to auction 'wtb tasarins grimoire/velishouls tome pages!' if you dont want to have to find them all yourself. <br>
<br>
people will usually accept breeze and 1pp for each page.  <br>
