---------------------------------------<br>
If you can't find anyone to group with and want decent experience for soloing from around 26 to 34 (a bit boring after a while, but decent exp), you can solo the Dwarves in OOT on Sister Isle. I tried many different spell strategies to minimize downtime between spawns, but this is what worked best for me: (1) Summon an animation, root/enstill the Dwarf from afar. (2) Tashani the Dwarf to lower MR. (3) I'd then lay in with Suffocate (DoT). By this time the male dwarves will break Enstill, but believe it or not Root seems to hold much longer (at least in almost every test it seemed to). (4) Chaos Flux (DD). (5) As the Dwarf runs up and hits you, let pet beat on dwarf as you Color Flux/Shift. (6) Backup a bit and re-root/enstill. (7) Chaos Flux again. And you can rinse and repeat steps 5 through 7. Done. Sit and med for next spawn. I was able to do this very successfully without losing a pet. I hear you can do the dwarves till 34, but I got bored and stopped at around 32. <br>
<br>
Xelbaaz Zzyzzx <br>
Enchanter of Tarew Marr <br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
ANOTHER GOOD STRATEGY FOR DWARVES IN OOT <br>
-----------------------------------------<br>
First, get your pet. You will need SoW for this strategy, so shout to trade clarity for sow, and you'll usually find someone willing to come. Get SoW for you and your pet. Now root the dwarf. Suffocate and DD (alternate your 2 best DD's to chain cast) until root breaks. Let the dwarf hit you once, and then run around the island, staying just out of reach of the dwarf. Hopefully, the dwarf will frenzy on you and ignore your pet. Your pet will follow behind, smacking the dwarf. Occasionally you'll need to turn around and DD it because it will stop frenzying, but that isn't too often. If the root was resisted, let the dwarf hit you, back up, and nuke him till he frenzies you. At level 29 I was able to take a dwarf using under 2 bubbles of mana with this strategy, so you can take at least 2 of the dwarves, maybe even all 3. <br>
<br>
