It's been a while, but let me see if I can give you some general info on soloing spectres.<br>
<br>
I think I started on them when the AC in UGuk quit giving me exp.  At 34, it will probably be touch and go, but do-able. You will certainly live, if you decide to run early enough. <br>
<br>
I've found the most difficult thing to do was to pull a fight I could handle. Usually the whole island of five is up there. <br>
<br>
Have SoW, and cast Illusion: Air Elemental, and have Rune III up. Best you can do is charm one, which will pull 3-5. Your charmed spec will taunt, and get agro off you, and at that point, you'd better start rooting them as fast as you can.<br>
<br>
The other specs will tear through your pet, but they'll be rooted at least when he dies.<br>
<br>
Charm another, repeat.  Do that until you have two left. Med while the specs thin down their numbers, and you should be fine. Then charm one, and drop a dot and a slow on the other. Sit down, and med up. That should give your pet the edge he needs to come out of the fight the winner, but bloody as hell. A root/nuke should finish off your pet when charm breaks.<br>
<br>
It's actually pretty easy to solo any number of specs, as long as you can manage agro, and keep the spectres rooted.<br>
<br>
Make sure to have all your self buffs up, (cha, ac, hp, mr, etc.).<br>
